This article is a transcript of President Joe Biden's speech at the celebration of the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA). He praised the advocates who worked hard to make the country more accessible and just. Biden highlighted the importance of the ADA, which was signed into law 32 years ago, and how it has changed the lives of Americans with disabilities. He mentioned the progress his administration has made in protecting the rights of workers with disabilities, creating new jobs, and increasing access to healthcare. Biden also emphasized the importance of disability pride and celebrated the younger generation for their acceptance and talent. The article concludes with the introduction of a blind pianist named José André Montaño, who performed at the event.